cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the application of deep convolutional neural networks for medical image analysis, specifically for identifying hemorrhages in CT head image volumes. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of multiple instance learning (MIL) is a key aspect of the paper, which is a supervised learning methodology that has gained traction for learning from weak labels. This makes the paper relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the data requirements for achieving accurate per-slice hemorrhage detection, which is related to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is a sub-field of multimedia (cs.MM).
